data.title: Reverberations Session 2
data.description:
Archived on 2025-09-21, this archive contains 960 messages between 9:43:10 PM to 2:39:57 AM.
					It has 29 dice rolls.

messages.content: Reverberations - Session 2
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Unknown date, 2007. Jacob J. Kavitz Federal Building, NYC, NY.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Diaz enters the smoky, refurbished room in one of the higher floors of the building.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: She knocks on the door twice and enters without waiting for a response, like told.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
She clears her throat.

"I expected something bigger, the office in Norfolk beats this."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Renovations in progress."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He is leaning against the huge window, smoking a cigarette.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Do you know why I called you here?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "To admit that we are finally square?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
"After this, perhaps."

He waves a manila folder.

"It's insanity. To a level that I have just my own stamp on it, with nobody elses."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Better have a plan that works now, isn't that what you've been doing all your life?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
He smirks.

"This is your own death warrant as much as it is your agents'. You know you won't get to walk this off, even with our help."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I have my reservations. Do you have anything else for me?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "No. I just wanted to relive the old times, even for a moment. Dusty rooms, after-hour meets. It used to be better back then."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He takes a long drag out of his cigarette.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Go spend time with your family. It's almost Christmas."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Your sense of humor is sick, as always."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: ABQ
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Samantha, you're up first.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You spent most of the drive here quiet and reserved. Out of all these fools, you recognize Doug but not the others.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You decided against a face-to-face with Schrader. Instead, you went around the block and personally visited some landmarks. Including the Days Inn Motel.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: There is enough vacancy for the whole party.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: But that's not it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You also dropped by a friendly that you got named, by the name of "Caldera".
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Civilian, veterinary. In the game. Not the Delta Green game, the 'crime' game.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Let's take a look.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's around dusk. You enter the pet clinic and walk past the secretary. She does not really bother you because it's not often someone shows up here in a business suit holding no pet.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You eventually come to the clinic room, with an operating table for small animals in the middle. Your guy is on the phone.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He leans into it, his back facing you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Yeah, don't forget to bring around lil' Smoky in two weeks for a parasite shot and a vaccine, okay?…"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The business here looks legit by all means.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Cliff walks by the bed and places a hand on it, staring at Caldera. When she's noticed, she gives a nod as an understanding to continue the call.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: "…Mmm, yeah. I got it. We'll mail you a reminder, thank you, have a nice day."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He turns around to face you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He immediately notices the lack of animals and business casual on your body.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "What, am I under arrest, agent?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You may speak and act freely.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
Cliff smiles. She lifts her hand off the bed, and raises it towards Caldera for a handshake.

"Of course not, Dr. Caldera."
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: "Well, then, how can I help you?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Well- how can he help me?
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Roll HUMINT.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Public.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

Samantha appears to be in her thirties with a comely nose and a sharp face. She's of average height, and aging has only recently started to creep in her features. She's of average weight, with dirty blonde hair and brown eyes. Furrows have started to form on her temple.

Samantha was interested in medicine from the moment

she listened to her father's heartbeat through his

stethescope. Smart and disciplined, she pushed through

a difficult education to become a trauma surgeon at the

NYU Grossman School of Medicine. By her early

thirties, she had already carved herself a reputation as a

skilled clinician and an accomplished researcher,

working to further the field of emergency medicine.

That reputation was tested the night her husband was

brought into her own hospital. He had been attacked,

initial reports indicating a mugging-gone-wrong.

Samantha was on call and prepared to operate, but

what she found was wrong; his bones and organs were

liquefied, and his vascular system ruptured in patterns

no aneurysm or illness could possibly explain.

She barely had time to process it before the body was

taken from her custody. Within hours, the chart was

scrubbed, and official records listed his death as a “

catastrophic hemorrhage.” Samantha, however,

remembered every detail. She knew what she saw, and

she knew someone else had made sure she wouldn't be

allowed to prove it.

Crushed but undeterred, she redirected her career.

Using her skills and connections, she entered the FBI’

Criminal Investigative Division as a forensic medical

specialist. For her past colleagues, it was a career

move. Secretly, it was a window for her to pursue her

own investigations regarding her husband's death.

Without telling anyone, she dug through case files:

unexplained autopsies, anomalies in forensic reports,

events that echoed what she’d seen on her husband’

s table.

She never said a word of her search to colleagues,

friends, or family. But Delta Green noticed.

Unauthorized queries, repeated hits on redacted case

numbers, her name appearing again and again where it

shouldn’t. They had already erased her husband’s

corpse, his grave had always been empty. Now, they

noticed they had left a loose end.

When they finally reached out, Samantha didn’t resist.

She'd been waiting for someone to admit what she

already knew: her husband’s death wasn’t natural.

Husband's death preceded Samantha's induction into the FBI and Delta Green by a few years. (Inducted into the FBI in 2000, DG in 2006) Before that time, the family was peaceful. Afterwards, she decided to send her son to boarding school, leaving home at the age of 13. She only sees her son in the summers, with the rare visit to his out-of-state school. Nowadays he's off to college, calling only out of necessity and a need for money. He's still affectionate towards her, but resents her for leaving him all by himself. One could say she doesn't know her own son.

messages.content: He really doesn't get the point or understand what's going on. You have to sweet talk him into it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I thought this guy was a friendly? Am I out of the loop
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: He IS a friendly, you can probably tell right out of the bat that he was not expecting a woman.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: An introduction is in order.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He snorts and scratches his nose nervously.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
Cliff keeps a soft smile as she keeps her hand raised for a shake.

"I'm Special Agent Cliff. I'll be your point of contact with the bureau."
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content:
He blows a huge gust of air from the corners of his lips as his cheeks swell up.

"Please, let's not say that out loud again here, or ever."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I'm in good standing with you folks, whatever you need just come here and pretend you're not a feeb, alright."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Of course. You won't get any trouble from us. This is just an introduction for further business, so you need not be alarmed."
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: "Right, I got the surgical theatre here, but I'd have to put you in the garage if you showed up at daytime."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Meds, tools, goons, other crap I dare not utter, I can arrange it."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "If you're new in town I could show you around, maybe grab dinner too, heh."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He laughs once to himself and realizes it's inappropiate.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
Cliff keeps a straight face.

"Well, I'm sure we can find the time to introduce you to the team…"
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: "Oh no, oh fuck no don't bring your 'team' here for a move-in party, please."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "In fact if you don't have another request it's about time you should go."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
Cliff tucks her lips and nods several times.

"Yup, about what I wanted to cover anyways. Hopefully we won't be in touch often."
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: She turns around to leave as she raises a hand goodbye.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: "I'll get some O- blood stocked and a human-sized defilibrator arranged, or something."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Bye now!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He goes back to work, going through phone calls.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
2130.

David is 'busy', rest of you have gathered nearby Studio Overground to take a look.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: There he goes..
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I should make that faster soon. Anyhow, you're all gathered in front of Studio Overground. It's nightttime.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You can hear the music booming from here. It's in the better part of the hood, so it's obvious why this place hasnt been shut down due to noise complaints yet.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A bouncer is vigorously bodysearching the patrons in the line and claiming that doors close in 15 minutes.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon. You're in the lead. What do you do?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: How's the disposition of the people look like? What's tonight's crowd like?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Cars are whizzing past. There's a taco truck feeding hungry lowlives a bit ahead.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The disposition of the people- ravegoers. All sorts of crazy, half naked clothing and strange hair. Most are skinny, down to the bone.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Some business casual people have also gotten in.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The crowd is calmer compared to a weekend in the club. If you were here yesterday on a Sunday it would be teeming, you guess.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's still big but not explosive big.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Are we tangoing with our guns at our hips or did we deign to leave them somewhere for this stakeout?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Your guns are carefully hidden below your jackets. No one is taking them off of you if you show your DEA badge. You know that.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The artillery is still in the trunk.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: What's the likelihood of getting fast-tracked inside if one or two of us flash our badges?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: 100%. Obstructing a federal investigation is not a charge someone is going to catch over 15$/h nightshift.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Now we're talking. Who else volunteers to enter tweaker MDMA heaven?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: There is nothing interesting going on outside. You don't see any of the MDMA dealers themselves, not from this angle. They don't tend to fuck around cartel territory- that is if the rumors are true and the owner is leashed to the Sinaloa.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan meekly offers to stay outside, just in case, and maybe see if there's any interesting traffic around the sides or back as the night goes on.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Whatever McCannon has planned could probably do with a Doug. He's in
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Finnegan, you're gang unit for fucks sake.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: What are you getting paid for?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You think to yourself exactly that.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon loves the idea of bald and anxious tagging along.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Earle graciously declines, for what he understands to be obvious reasons.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: …Well, someone has to keep America safe. Let's go.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Cinco de Mayo, right. That's reasons
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content:
Bathroom run.

You are all grouped up in a "parking lot" (vacant private property with a bunch of cars) discussing your next move. Be done with it until I return.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon volunteers Samantha to also come along. He doesn't really care if Finnegan and Earle want to gorge themselves on al pastor.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Cliff readily agrees to come along.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: You people smell that?
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: 'Ethnic' is in the air tonight
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: McCannon, did you miss your Ambien schedule? You don't know a "Pastor" yet.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: This is a golden oppurtunity to secure some reverb for personal uses. Wink wink.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's food, man, people gotta eat.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: You are entering the nightclub a la feebie clown car. The bouncer at the door doesn't even dare to stop you, and you're inside single file.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: For posterity sake, is McCannon leading the way? At the head of the line?
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Yes, and being blasted by the godawful electronic music first.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: The music is booming. Enough to silence casual conversation.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You may move.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Roll Alertness.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

Brown hair and small, baby blue eyes, of average height and build.

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

messages.content: The smell of sweating bodies is overwhelming, despite the powerful AC fans.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Fixed to the ceiling are crystal "cages" with performers inside them, half naked. They are throwing it down, 6 of them arranged in a polgyonal pattern above the dance floor.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Light is reflecting off of them in crazy angles.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Wrong scene
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content:
In front of you is a reception desk where you may turn in your car keys to get "stamped" on the hand. You just saw it get done to a guy, the stamp is the logo of the club.

Its a cartoon cactus with a snapback cap and a boombox.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You may act.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Hey, welcome."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Party of five," McCannon pulls out the badge from his jacket pocket and unfurls it towards the bouncer, "Business, not pleasure."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Right on."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He speaks into his earpiece.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon waves the people behind him forward.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "What next?"
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "We look like a bunch of schnooks…"
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: The crowd is dancing exactly like what 300mg ecstasy feels like.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The group is just past the doors and the music is starting to give Doug Moore a headache.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: As far as you can tell nobody cares about your presence yet.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "We are a bunch of schnooks. For starters, did any of you grab the printouts? Finnegan?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: What printouts?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan has a copy of the Spider brochure.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Missing person pictures?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Camera pictures.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Oh, also the file.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's a copy, though, not the original.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: skel is afk
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: "I think we should ask ask about the Lucas kid. He might've been a regular."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "That's what I was thinking. Hey, man," McCannon waves at the bouncer as he shuffles back to him. "Big man in?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: You are starting to get some weird stares from the tables around you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "He's in the private room."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Where is it at?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: He points you northeast.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Might want to get a move on."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: skel is back
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: You can move your tokens right?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You May Walk
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Right on. Doug, Samantha, go get a drink and make conversation with the bartender. Frank, Dick, let's get to private."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Oh."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Right."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Ehe."
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: If you are having trouble use the arrow keys.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A guy dancing like it's his last day on earth shoulders you very roughly.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Roll Strength.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

Brown hair and small, baby blue eyes, of average height and build.

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

messages.content: You stand still like a tree. He staggers to his knees.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Sorry, man! Sorry!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He goes deeper into the mosh, escaping.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Don't mind me. You just have fun." He flashes a creepy smile in his direction as he recedes.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Samantha, just so you know, the bar is south.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You should be able to see past the windows.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Agent? Uh, Samantha?" Doug gets in close and lowers his voice, though they are quite a distance away from any person and barely audible as is.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: You can't even hear what you are saying at this tone.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Right, clearly not.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Cliff leans in, moving her ear closer to Moore.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: McCannon. You're at the private rooms, it's in front of you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: What now?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: More of a halfhearted yell: "Samantha, how is it going to look when two uniformed feebees come up to the bar? How will we play this?!"
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Doors not seethrough? No slit?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Feel free to act, Finnegan and Earle.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Nope. Bank vault solid. Or drywall solid, it doesn't matter. The music is really getting to your nerves, McCannon.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Earle's simply following McCannon's lead and awkwardly averting his eyes from any nearby women.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Finnegan looks at McCannon. "Do you want to ask the questions? I can think of a couple."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Earle.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Roll Charisma.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
Samantha leans into Moore's ear, coming off somewhat loud this close up.

"We had some presentation and hit the bar. Accounting maybe?"
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI
TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

Slightly overweight, brown hair combed to one side, chevron moustache.

a- Born 1980 in Paris Texas to a single mother. Rough upbringing led him to (mostly) forswear drugs and alcohol, developed a complex against middle America, 'hicks' etc.

- Became interested in computer science during the dot-com bubble and left home to study I.T at 18.

- Married in 2003 while working the help-desk at Cisco. Made the majority of his income at this time via cable piracy - running services that could decrypt smart cards, set-top boxes etc.

- Became interested in libertarianism and conspiracy culture at around this time, which tied into much of his hacking work; claims to have worked with Gary McKinnon, among others.

- Joined FBI Operational Technology division in 2005, in part for work experience and in part to enter the 'belly of beast' as far as his interests are concerned ('is the government really messing with the weather?' etc).

- Continues to work in this capacity alongside his side-hustles; regarded by colleagues as reliable, if a little eccentric.

messages.content: "Suppose..? Might pay to ask about that kid, assuming the others have any success."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Shall we?"
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Let's go."
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: A black woman splayed on the couch right next to you waves her dainty fingers towards your direction, saying "hiiii" through thin lips.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "If you've got anything that you'd like to shoot immediately go right ahead. The music is giving me a headache and I'll think of something when we get somewhere insulated from the cacophony."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: She takes a sip out of a drink.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The crowd cheers the DJ as the song comes to an end and a new one begins.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Trust me, it's not my type, either." Can we knock on the door?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: You knock on the door. No response. It's locked, try banging.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Continue moving.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I give it a FLETC-grade knock.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: I give it a FLETC-grade knock.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content:
BANG BANG BANG.

A voice from the inside says, "WHAAT?!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Front desk called ahead. Open up!"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Not sure how to handle the sudden attention he nods cowboy-style to the black lady before returning to the group.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Doors to your right.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The bouncer guy gets up from his chair and peers the door enough to see you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Who the fuck are you bro?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "DEA. We've got a few questions. Nobody is in any trouble."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Fucking crackers from DEA."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Alright, alright."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Get off me bitch."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Just open the damn door."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Uh… That thing you mentioned, Agent…" He's talking to Samantha, more whispering.  The music is not as deafiningly loud in the little walled off bar area.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: He dusts off and arrives at the door.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Forgot to mention I don't know the first thing about accounting." Maybe he's giving himself too little credit. Still, that's what Doug thinks.  "Not going to affect anything, right?"
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Hey. My office, alright. Right across."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I am not much for small talk. Mind asking the questions?"
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Sure thing." I step back enough to give him comfortable space to lead the way.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "You ladies wait for daddy, ahahahahahah."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Don't fret over it. Just be casual."
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: "Come on."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug forgot "casual" a decade ago. He is trying hard to recall how to.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: He raises an impressed eyebrow at the Spanish fellow's retinue of ladies.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: This room is very clearly insulated. The music comes to a hum.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Cliff sits down first, sighing as she settles into her seat.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: "So, what can I do for you agents?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You got me at a busy hour."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I can tell, it looks like you do well here." No forced smiles.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Doug thinks this is something like a game of pantomime so he sits down, as well, and sighs, as well, but it comes out notably deeper and more exasperated. Must be all the stress.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: McCannon takes the liberty of sitting down in one of the cush chairs.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: There's another patron at the bar with Samantha and Doug. Probably no-one
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Doug, Samantha. The bartender will talk to you shortly. For now you're waiting for the drinks you asked for to pour.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Yees, make yourself at home."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Now what do you have for me?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan takes the photograph of Lucas out of his jacket and puts it on the table. "I'd like you to look at this picture. Do you know this man?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: He gestures to the bouncer, as well. "You, as well, please."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "No greetings first?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It takes a moment, but he remembers that you are in fact not the feds that he reports to.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Agent Callahan. We're in from El Paso."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "And you, dick beater?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He lights a cigarillo.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Be civil, now. I guarantee you there's at least a dozen people out there melting their brains off of ecstasy, if not all of them, and we can tie this place up in so much federal tape that this club will be silent for the forseeable future. "
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "And it's Agent Woods."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Hey look now, my club is clean."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "They call me Cucaracha here, okkkay? And it's because I went to federal for a bullshit charge where I got shanked twice and almost died. But I don't fucking die to that. And there are no fucking dealers in here or out there in my property."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I can't stop people shooting up and then coming here for a dance, alright."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "It's entertainment."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "We've heard good things and we're not here to roll up a bunch of kids out for a night on the town." He taps the photo.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Rodriguez, pour a glass of Zafir each for my guests. Let's sweeten this up."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The bouncer begins pouring up from a blue bottle with a spiky cap. Some of you know this thing, a shot is 50$ usually.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He drinks his own and then demands the photo from your hands.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's on the table for him to do with as he wishes.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "You know it'd help the image if you had people address you by your government name instead of the cholo shit, you feel me?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content:
He scratches his fat chin.

"Don't know him. Never seen or talked to him. They say he was last seen here before he vanished but the only thing cops found was a blown up toilet stall."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Come on man, you got the papers, you got the forensics, fiiiigure it out."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He leans forward to take his shot glass and, hoping to make up for the cold reception they're getting, quickly imbibes - before puckering his lips and cringing a little like he just got hit in the face.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: The liquor is very refined and aromatic. It goes down effortlessly despite the fireball taste.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan leaves his drink untouched. "He's not the only person who was last seen hanging out around here. Like you said, it's entertainment, a clean business, I'm not trying to bust your balls… But lightning doesn't generally strike twice."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "I don't know what the fucking law people think about my club, coming here for a missing persons case every week, do you think I have a hole to the center of earth here?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Look, you know what? There is the CCTV computer."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He points at the table behind the bodyguard.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan looks back at Earle and gestures with his head.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: McCannon looks at Earle: "Agent?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "It's all yours. But I have no business with no missing people."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Eeeyup." A quick nod and he's on his way, set on scraping all the data he can on here to his laptop.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Roll Intelligence.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.

Slightly overweight, brown hair combed to one side, chevron moustache.

a- Born 1980 in Paris Texas to a single mother. Rough upbringing led him to (mostly) forswear drugs and alcohol, developed a complex against middle America, 'hicks' etc.

- Became interested in computer science during the dot-com bubble and left home to study I.T at 18.

- Married in 2003 while working the help-desk at Cisco. Made the majority of his income at this time via cable piracy - running services that could decrypt smart cards, set-top boxes etc.

- Became interested in libertarianism and conspiracy culture at around this time, which tied into much of his hacking work; claims to have worked with Gary McKinnon, among others.

- Joined FBI Operational Technology division in 2005, in part for work experience and in part to enter the 'belly of beast' as far as his interests are concerned ('is the government really messing with the weather?' etc).

- Continues to work in this capacity alongside his side-hustles; regarded by colleagues as reliable, if a little eccentric.

messages.content: The chances of you failing to pull the CCTV footage is next to none. However, with the extra time, you can pretend you're doing just that while smartly doing something else.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Any other thing you wish to look for on this computer or network?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He checks to see if the PC is linked to Cuca-coockoo's emails or some other database that'd be of interest of them.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: It is. You find a ton of financial e-mails and correspondence from any provider a nightclub might need. Audio engineers, catering, all that.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Your Accounting 10% is worthless to determine any discrepancies.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: However, Internet is a series of pipes. You have one more move.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finally he looks for any files on here that are encrypted, password locked, otherwise out of place. Anything that'd be worth checking on later on his laptop.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Nothing here is encrypted. However, this does tell something. He is old fashioned and keeps his passwords on a physical piece of paper, et al. Probably. The most out of place thing you can see are some digital photos of him with other thugs. And that's not even that "out of place" either, considering the mans history.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You finished?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Something like that." He says, sniffing and heading back with the other two.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Earle, you narrow the footage down to 30 minutes of Lucas entering the club and vanishing into thin air. On 3x playback, it will take 10 minutes at the least for you to analyze it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: In the mean time, I take it that McCannon and Finnegan are investigating "the toilet"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It'd better not be a stupid joke. Yes.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Yep.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Cucaracha gets up out of his white leather chair and corrects his jacket.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I'll be here for a few more, before I return to my girls."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "If there is anything you need to help me get these punks off my back, let me know."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I really do have nothing to do with these putas anymore."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "And I want it to stay that way."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "We appreciate the help." Finnegan collects the photos. "It's dirty business. We want it off the streets just as much as you want it out of your business."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: fix my screen pls!
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: After a customary nod, you are leaving Earle to watch the footage in the office as you go to the bathrooms.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Feel free to move. It's right south of the office, the toilets.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: On the way through the main room, Finnegan scans the crowd - ABQ isn't the most cosmopolitan city - on the lookout for any unusual groups of Oriental types, maybe lingering around the peripheral or in a group.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Roll Search.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon just marches the toilets. He's a million miles away in his own world.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8
PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd
messages.content:
Success

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.

messages.content: You would be right. Majority is white trash, but there are a couple blacks and asians scattered about.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Out of anything unusual…
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Well, there are 2 Asian girls in that corner over there, and both do not seem on the pill.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Right down west of you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: To McCannon. "You think he's bullshitting? We've got him on solicitation, at least enough to twist his arm. That's five girls of the same persuasion in the same club. Might be a connection to our tong."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Of course he's bullshitting. He's making too much money on this shit. It's imperative for him that he's bullshitting."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: It's a free country.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Both of you are at the doors of the bathrooms.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: We are panning to Samantha and Doug.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finish your sentence.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Yeah I go by La Cucaracha but noooooo I'm not part of the cartel. Fuck off."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Doug is at the bar, waiting for his daiquiri to get there. That thing must have the consistency of prehistoric tree resin, considering how long it's taking to pour and mix.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "There you go, enjoy."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Anything else I can get you?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Right on, thanks."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Doug kind of relied on Samantha for this. The man is not much for gathering intelligence by way of small talk.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: He artfully spins and flips some mixer around and pours syrups and whatnot in some crazy cocktail.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He's a white boy, clean shaven and all.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Well, if that's how it is going to be…
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: The situation, sitting at a bar and asking the bartender this, is cliche enough to make Doug's jaw lock up but here he goes.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Say, what's the word around here lately?"
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Anything… interesting happening?"
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: He grimaces.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "The show yesterday was pretty good."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Yeah. Yeah, I bet it was."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "They got smoke effects and all."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: What was he expecting?
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Place must be doing pretty good. How long you been here?"
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: "A little over four months. Gotta make ends meet for college."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "It's nicer than my last gig."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Oh, I used to bartend in college. What do you study?"
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: "Law."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He's rubbing down on a glass now.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Must be quite the hustle."
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Doug is going at that Daiquiri like it's the blood of Christ. Who knew that having drinks on this job was a thing? Just a little bit, though. Just to get a taste.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "I like it."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

Samantha appears to be in her thirties with a comely nose and a sharp face. She's of average height, and aging has only recently started to creep in her features. She's of average weight, with dirty blonde hair and brown eyes. Furrows have started to form on her temple.

Samantha was interested in medicine from the moment

she listened to her father's heartbeat through his

stethescope. Smart and disciplined, she pushed through

a difficult education to become a trauma surgeon at the

NYU Grossman School of Medicine. By her early

thirties, she had already carved herself a reputation as a

skilled clinician and an accomplished researcher,

working to further the field of emergency medicine.

That reputation was tested the night her husband was

brought into her own hospital. He had been attacked,

initial reports indicating a mugging-gone-wrong.

Samantha was on call and prepared to operate, but

what she found was wrong; his bones and organs were

liquefied, and his vascular system ruptured in patterns

no aneurysm or illness could possibly explain.

She barely had time to process it before the body was

taken from her custody. Within hours, the chart was

scrubbed, and official records listed his death as a “

catastrophic hemorrhage.” Samantha, however,

remembered every detail. She knew what she saw, and

she knew someone else had made sure she wouldn't be

allowed to prove it.

Crushed but undeterred, she redirected her career.

Using her skills and connections, she entered the FBI’

Criminal Investigative Division as a forensic medical

specialist. For her past colleagues, it was a career

move. Secretly, it was a window for her to pursue her

own investigations regarding her husband's death.

Without telling anyone, she dug through case files:

unexplained autopsies, anomalies in forensic reports,

events that echoed what she’d seen on her husband’

s table.

She never said a word of her search to colleagues,

friends, or family. But Delta Green noticed.

Unauthorized queries, repeated hits on redacted case

numbers, her name appearing again and again where it

shouldn’t. They had already erased her husband’s

corpse, his grave had always been empty. Now, they

noticed they had left a loose end.

When they finally reached out, Samantha didn’t resist.

She'd been waiting for someone to admit what she

already knew: her husband’s death wasn’t natural.

Husband's death preceded Samantha's induction into the FBI and Delta Green by a few years. (Inducted into the FBI in 2000, DG in 2006) Before that time, the family was peaceful. Afterwards, she decided to send her son to boarding school, leaving home at the age of 13. She only sees her son in the summers, with the rare visit to his out-of-state school. Nowadays he's off to college, calling only out of necessity and a need for money. He's still affectionate towards her, but resents her for leaving him all by himself. One could say she doesn't know her own son.

messages.content: It just seems like an usual bar for a rave club.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You need to get creative, the two of you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Odd to have a bar walled off like this from the dance floor nowadays."
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: "It's good, very good."
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: "Yeah, no holding drinks on the dance floor."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug still has his eyes on the patron sitting to his left. Are they relevant in any way to the situation at hand? Are they anyone at all?
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Makes a huuge mess."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: All you can see is…
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A middle-aged Hispanic woman.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: She looks uninterested for small talk.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Noted. This is not anything.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: The world is your oyster. You have 2 minutes to spin this encounter into something useful before we pan back to McCannon.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug is not oblivious enough to miss that McCannon might have just wanted these two out of the way. He doesn't comment. Well, in that case…
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Being a bad investigator on purpose is usually not a part of a plan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: 60 seconds.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug is more of a feeling person than a thinking person. Conversation aside, anything stands out, in particular? Probably not.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Just some white kid…
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Do you usually get interesting clientele? Me and my buddy here are merchants of sorts, sometimes of some more unique items…"
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Samantha. Roll Persuasion. That sounded fucking unhinged, so at a -20%.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug cocks an eyebrow to 120% of regular eyebrow cocking measure.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: He closes in on the counter.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

Samantha appears to be in her thirties with a comely nose and a sharp face. She's of average height, and aging has only recently started to creep in her features. She's of average weight, with dirty blonde hair and brown eyes. Furrows have started to form on her temple.

Samantha was interested in medicine from the moment

she listened to her father's heartbeat through his

stethescope. Smart and disciplined, she pushed through

a difficult education to become a trauma surgeon at the

NYU Grossman School of Medicine. By her early

thirties, she had already carved herself a reputation as a

skilled clinician and an accomplished researcher,

working to further the field of emergency medicine.

That reputation was tested the night her husband was

brought into her own hospital. He had been attacked,

initial reports indicating a mugging-gone-wrong.

Samantha was on call and prepared to operate, but

what she found was wrong; his bones and organs were

liquefied, and his vascular system ruptured in patterns

no aneurysm or illness could possibly explain.

She barely had time to process it before the body was

taken from her custody. Within hours, the chart was

scrubbed, and official records listed his death as a “

catastrophic hemorrhage.” Samantha, however,

remembered every detail. She knew what she saw, and

she knew someone else had made sure she wouldn't be

allowed to prove it.

Crushed but undeterred, she redirected her career.

Using her skills and connections, she entered the FBI’

Criminal Investigative Division as a forensic medical

specialist. For her past colleagues, it was a career

move. Secretly, it was a window for her to pursue her

own investigations regarding her husband's death.

Without telling anyone, she dug through case files:

unexplained autopsies, anomalies in forensic reports,

events that echoed what she’d seen on her husband’

s table.

She never said a word of her search to colleagues,

friends, or family. But Delta Green noticed.

Unauthorized queries, repeated hits on redacted case

numbers, her name appearing again and again where it

shouldn’t. They had already erased her husband’s

corpse, his grave had always been empty. Now, they

noticed they had left a loose end.

When they finally reached out, Samantha didn’t resist.

She'd been waiting for someone to admit what she

already knew: her husband’s death wasn’t natural.

Husband's death preceded Samantha's induction into the FBI and Delta Green by a few years. (Inducted into the FBI in 2000, DG in 2006) Before that time, the family was peaceful. Afterwards, she decided to send her son to boarding school, leaving home at the age of 13. She only sees her son in the summers, with the rare visit to his out-of-state school. Nowadays he's off to college, calling only out of necessity and a need for money. He's still affectionate towards her, but resents her for leaving him all by himself. One could say she doesn't know her own son.

Brown hair and small, baby blue eyes, of average height and build.

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

Brown hair and small, baby blue eyes, of average height and build.

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The porcelain bits lay scattered and the sewer pipe is otherwise exposed.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: There is charring on the sides.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "The fuck? Finnegan, try and make sense of this clusterfuck for me."

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.

messages.content: The sense deepens. It's just not right. A pulse of coldness washes over your heart, the exact same you felt like when you got rejected by a girl in high school for the first time. However, it lasts infinitely short, like a light being flicked on and off.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You come to your senses and notice the geometrical charring patterns across the walls.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Dozens and dozens of polygonally-shaped burn marks.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: In triangles, rectangles, polyhedrons, etc.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: And that's not it. It does not encroach just an inch outside of the stall.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's like if the apocalypse happened inside of this tiny enclosed space but nothing else reflected out of it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He squints through his glasses. "…I'd say take a sample. Whatever happened in here was… I don't know, some kind of very strange chemical reaction. I don't know what to say."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "But we're not here long enough to get results. God."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: As soon as you pick up a ceramic shard, you notice that it's disintegrated into a very precise geometric shape of…
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: 17 sides.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I don't know if I'm seeing what you're seeing. What's up?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Understandably, he marvels at it for a little longer than is appropriate.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: You drop it into a zip-loc bag, eventually.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It can't be more than a scattered piece of toilet, right?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I've just never seen something break like this. Especially ceramic, you know. It's… Perfect." Any human remains? Clothing shreds, parts of a shoe, personal effects?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Roll Search.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Is McCannon seeing the same thing as Finnegan?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: +20% with help.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.

messages.content: McCannon, you're just looking at a blast crater.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: However the shards are indisputable.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Do they look like regular porcelain shards to me?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Finnegan, you take way too long with your scrutiny and come to the realization that not one smidge of human trace is inside this stall.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: No, they are in perfectly cut shapes.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Even worse. "I know this whole place is probably popping positive, but maybe the kid was mixing something, I mean…" I open the bag and want to use the Defender on it, the sniffer device.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Both of you get your shit together, collecting evidence to the best of your ability. Pieces of debris clutter up your jacket pockets.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I'm not sure I follow, man. Did they use an angle grinder on this thing or what?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Really not much to look at besides broken crap.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Right. Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Let's see. No need to roll. Do let it do its job inside the baggy.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I'm not sure. Something obviously happened here. The scorches, they're almost… Fractal, like the pieces. The only thing I can think of is some kind of really particular… Well, no shame in saying I just don't know. And there was an adult male here."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Finnegan. Remind me how precise and capable your device is when it comes to narcotics.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I don't see any fractal scorches, but I'll take your word for it. Would be wise to burn this whole joint down just because of this contamination, but we have neither the time or resources."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: It's a portable mass spectrometer that can return a quick positive (false or not) on particulate of common narcotics and explosive residues.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Positive.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Clearly something is in the mix.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: That's about as much as you get out of this thing.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: MDMA? Nitroglycerine? Maybe too mixed to determine. That wasn't much help.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Trace amounts of MDMA.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He shakes his head. "Just a little bit of MDMA, but maybe it liquified some piss when the rest of the room flared. There's just no way this happened without someone hearing or seeing something."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Any other thing you wish to do here?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: We don't have a timeline to make prints or lab analysis worth our while. McCannon?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Not required, not applicable. Let's reconvene with Earle. Maybe we can ask if Cucaracha's seen this shit.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: It's 2008, you can sort most of it out in a few hours save for full spectrum DNA analysis.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: That, will take a few days.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I hate to say it, but the only thing I can think of is that someone tampered with this. It's not cleaned up - why? Someone else has at least looked over it."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Common sense be told, Finnegan. When someone sees blown up toilet they think firecracker and dickheads, not missing person.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Let's pan over to Earle, after McCannon finishes.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Just another person in our great big list of people to be dealt with."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Fuck."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Finnegan, your holster uncomfortably tugs against the stall lock as you walk out. It's nothing, but it's sign that you might be losing your grip.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Do walk to the office.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Frank.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You got it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's been a good 15 minutes but you think that Lucas talked to this girl right before spiriting away.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's a brunette. (HOLD ON I'M UPLOADING A THING)
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You three get a good look at it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Bingo. What now?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Does Cucaracha recognize her?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Or the bouncer?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Both shrug it off.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan looks at the owner, trying to think of something sly to say about the stall. "And you're sure you never saw either of those gentlemen?" He falters.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "I don't know that white punk. I said it."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Ever heard the name 'Spider'?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "It's the dude who apparently vanished here a month ago. Yeah, the cops told me."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I don't know him in person."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "A dude who was pushing in your club."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "I don't know anything about that, we got great security."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Off the record, no one pushes anything inside here. My business is squeaky clean."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I'm sure. But I know you see how this looks from my end of the table."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Okay. Let's talk cards. What exactly do you have on me white boy?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "We don't want to make a scene. Do you really think we can't pick you up for solicitation?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "What solicitation?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Your three amigas in the other room. I'm not playing stupid with you, play straight with me. We want whatever this kid was into - bathroom blowout or not - and if we can do that without entangling you, that's fine in our book."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Roll Persuasion.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.

messages.content: "Alright, you think I'm a pimp, pimp? I barely know those girls besides their soft asses. You get me in the box for 24 hours, then what? I told you I don't know the damn kid. Even if I did I would never work for a greasy haired stoner piece of shit gringo like what you just showed me."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He does sound genuine.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: While the two are arguing Earle decides to push his luck. He opens the command prompt on the PC and starts typing some gibberish to see if anyone notices.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Earle. You open the command prompt and type in gibberish.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Then what?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan looks at McCannon. "I don't think you're turning anyone out, boss. I just think you like to keep a few girlfriends handy. I noticed there's a bit of a theme - they're not the only Asian girls here. Birds of a feather, you know." He stares down his glasses. "I think they might've known our Spider. Might've even mentioned him to you. Think hard."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Then he tries typing up a batch script that'll save any keystrokes on this PC to a notepad file on the same PC - a very primitive keylogger, in essence, that'd take someone getting a hold of this computer later on to use.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: "Maybe. Maybe I just got the yellow fever."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "But I'll let you in on it just so you get off my back already."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Those girls, they smoke some weird shit called 'Liao' and refuse to pass me one puff, ever."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Now you might be thinkin, did I just rat someone out? I said I don't know shit about them. And they refuse me a courtesy in my own place."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I've had enough of you people for one night."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "The feeling is mutual. We appreciate your cooperation."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: brb rq
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Richard.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Liao. Your mind goes back to Tcho-Tcho Study.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The enigmatic "nectar of heaven" mentioned multiple times in the book itself. It just doesn't match anything else.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It doesn't make sense. Some Chinese prostitutes, here in the United States have access to a ritual substance?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: And it's not something you can arrest them over. It's not illegal. Hell, no one even knows it. You'd be risking your badge.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I hate coincidences.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Are the effects of the drug described as I remember?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: He did not describe any of the effects. However, the way he talked about it… roll HUMINT
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.

messages.content: If it's casually imbibed in the company of others it must mean it's not a "real" drug like heroin or xanax.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Definitely something organic vice pharma. Smoked, that's good to know.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Many ways to skin this cat.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: List your actions if you have one, this scene is ending.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I'll bring it up to McCannon afterwards if there's time.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Within the nightclub I mean.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Negative.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: You there McCannon?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I'm here.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: I got nothing.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Excellent. You leave the nightclub in about the same casual air as you waltzed in.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: All in a day's work.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: He didn't do shit.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: We are taking a 10 minute break, you have physical and digital evidence of the disappearance. It's about 10:30PM and all of you are dead tired.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Consider your actions.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan has one thing to do outside the club before we drive off.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: What's that?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A cursory look at the parking lot. Looking for a blue Civic, vanity license plate.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Are you talking about Lucas' car?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Yes.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Smart. Yup, right here.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Looks like they didn't impound it yet.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Workload probably.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He points it out to McCannon. "That's how he got to the club. We should toss this before it gets towed. Might get lucky."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: More than one way to skin this cat. No roll to get in the very loud way, but lockpicking or otherwise finessing your way in is going to be hard to very hard.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Would it be a criminology roll?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Anyone here have some experience boosting cars? That's a loaded question in present company.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Not a Criminology roll.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Think. Hard.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A cop?
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Those with Drive 50% may know some tricks.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Jimmying the windshield trick?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Let's make sure the trunk is locked. If it isn't, we can get into the rear seats easily.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Not windshield, door window.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: One of you can risk an INT roll at -40% for a terrible insight.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Only one.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I got drive 50%.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: I'll give it a shot
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: This is a seperate thing on its own.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.
