messages.content: Nope.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Just no, you'll have to houdini your way in.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The trunk is locked.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "No two ways about it. Anyone got a glass breaker?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: In any case, it would be convenient for you if you thought with your Delta Green brain and not FBI brain.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Tricks from Drive 50%?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Getting in and wiring shut the alarm quick enough, but it will wake some people up anyway.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "A rock's a glass breaker. But no, not one you're thinking of, probably not."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Finnegan, there are two telescopic batonnes in the back of the chevy.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I'd have thought of slim jimming the window.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Instead of breaking it.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "You guys are gonna ruin your credibility doing this shit if anyone sees.2
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: "If you're worried about your credibility you're in the wrong line of work."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "We're six deep with badges and there's no telling when a meter maid is going to whisk this thing away to a lot. Boss, it's your call."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Looks like opinions are divided. Doug is not feeling this at all.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: The baton is whispering to you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: khoka is afk
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Finnegan retrives both and hands the other to Earle. "Who's got the alarm once we're in? We'll be fine, this could be our in."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Someone pop the hood and disconnect the battery. We've all see enough auto theft to know that's step one.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Y'still planning on playing DEA agent after this? Shiiiiiit."
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: khoka is back
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Let's get this open, bag it, tag it, and get some sleep. My head is pounding."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Unless anyone actually objects, Finnegan'll take a swing at the driver's side window.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: CRASH!!
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: BEEEEEEWEEEEEEEEEEBEEEEEEEEEWEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEBEEEEEEEEEEEEEEWEEEEEEEEEEE
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Oh for the love of--"
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Someone get the fucking glove box!" He opens the doors, flicks the locks and goes for the center console and the space under the driver's seat.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: McCannon rushes around the side and opens the side door, pulling open the glovebox.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The glovebox throws open.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Inside, a Ruger .380 hammerless revolver and a bag of pills.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Into the evidence bags they go.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: By its weight you'd say there's about 80 to 100 of them.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: They look exactly as they look, a bunch of Skype pills.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Is anyone checking the back? "Don't forget the floor mats." Finnegan blurts out.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Doug does.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: For anything else, highest Search in the party rolls.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: …Or not.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Hit it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

Brown hair and small, baby blue eyes, of average height and build.

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

messages.content: Finnegan takes anything and everything from the glove box, cup holders, center console - receipts, registration, insurance, and hustles back to the car, muttering something about "pattern of life".
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Seek for it and you shall find.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: If no other actions, all of you get into the federal battlebus and begin driving into the night.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He already started running the moment he realized he'd prove useless here. He clearly doesn't have the makings of a varsity athlete.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: From here you can either book the motel or take the 30 minute drive to safehouse.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's 10 minutes less at nighttime.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The motel does have vacancy and is shit cheap.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan wants to get this evidence off of his person and into the safehouse as soon as possible.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: It doesn't really matter, the hot potato is yours as long as you have the DEA badge on you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: And you will need a lab to analyze both.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug is just dead tired for no reason whatsoever. Safehouse it'd better be, but he's not driving.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Put someone behind the wheel and let's get some sleep at the safehouse.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: With no objections, you all drive to the safehouse.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Someone who isn't Richard J. Finnegan. He has rotten luck with cars, lately.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: After a shower and a beer each, you begin going to sleep one after other.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Someone who is not Samantha Cliff, M.D. She has rotten luck, in general.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: 10 minute break.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Informational.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: one thing you should note, cucaracha mentioned multiple missing person cases tying back to the nightclub
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: you didn't pick up on it on the spot
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Every week" or something to that effect.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: McCannon.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The clock says 2:30AM. Everyone else already dozed off. But you know it's a long shot for you without the Ambien.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You're making your report of the first day to Diaz over your laptop.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You're on TOR, connected to the "customer service" of a money transfer escrow scam. Matter of fact is, Allison is on the other side of the screen. Dawn must be breaking in D.C. about now.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Anything else besides the routine event report you want to get through?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon wants to examine that weird piece of porcelain himself. Maybe he'll see something Finnegan didn't.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "not over this."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "anything else?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: oh, you meant as in communication with Allison
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: aka. Diaz
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You make a quick jab at something unbelievable and you're instantly interrupted, basically.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Mostly complaining about the team of cats he is herding, but noting Finnegan's surprising initative and competency. And the fact that he saw something that McCannon didn't.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "don't let him lose his shit. you know what to do."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The chat closes.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You pop an amby and drift to a dreamless sleep. Everyone on prescriptions, subtract 1 from your inventory.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's Lorazepam, sir.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Then you have incredible dreams of childlike wonder… actually no you doze off and when you wake up it's 0800 sharp as a razor.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Dawn of the Second Day.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: List your actions, there is enough cereal and milk for everyone in the house but no one is stopping you from getting a better breakfast.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Rallying the group for breakfast at a Mexican joint.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Cereal and milk, are you kidding me? Time to go to a diner.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Oh, actually, what McCannon is having.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: McCannon.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You remember something from last night.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's still Cinco de Mayo out there, somewhere.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Last night he'd been talking to Doug, who he's been using as a bit of a blank slate, about how these days there are websites where you can order drugs for delivery like patio furniture. This morning he intended to chase that lead - in other words, cereal and milk for him. He's staying inside for the time being.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: You have a meeting arranged for 1600 today in a diner called "Golden Griddle" with an undercover DEA contact.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Diaz confirms he is not in the game and should be kept out of the loop.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Not friendly, just neutral, then.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Are we going somewhere, or eating in? It's window dressing, we have business to talk and eveidence to review.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: You don't even want to think about how many strings are being pulled behind this meet right now.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: In fact, what triggered this red flag in the first place?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The cell inside DEA must be really up to something.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Could be worth digging in to.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon does not give one fuck about milk and cereal given since he is a grown man. Huevos rancheros it is.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Could be worth digging into, but things are compartmentalized for a reason. Poking the hornets nest isn't in his plans right now.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: No one seems to object to the breakfast outing. You all find a Mexican restaurant that serves at this hour somewhere inside the city proper.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's 0920. You're really going through your time like it's a vacation.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's clearly putting Finnegan on edge, if nothing else.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: David is busy again today. The rest of you, you have evidence to analyze and doors to knock on.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Earle.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You have enough material on the woman to put through cyber forensics.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: However, bureucratically speaking, it will raise a lot of flags for DEA to arrest someone over a missing persons case.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: One of you will have to sweeten up the cops.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan. You have debris and a bag of Skype pills.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The heroic act of popping one at 0920 is still within the realm of possibility.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: With the appropriate gloves and mask, he wants to shave the corner off a pill and see what the analyzer spits back.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: MDMA.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: This really ain't it, a handheld laser pointer and a forensic lab are a comparison akin to a baby with the coughe and a hydrogen bombe.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Samantha could do great with this.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Right. We can section off some of this dope to go to an actual forensics lab. It'll help us figure out what he's into. Finnegan has a working phone, right?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: You have a burner phone and a no sim card Blackberry.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The burner will work just fine. He dials the number on Lucas' missing persons report for the Parole Officer.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content:
Brrrrrp. Brrrrrp. Brr-

"Hello? Who is this?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Good morning. Agent Callahan, DEA, El Paso? I was hoping you have time for a few questions about one of your parolees."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Oh, hello agent. Angela Martinez here. I take it this is about Lucas."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Yes, ma'am, Damien Lucas. I know he did some time other year - have you been with him since his release in '05?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Yees."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Are you aware that Damien is currently considered a missing person by the police?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "I'm aware. I was called when the report was submitted."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "He got off of probation months ago, it's so sad to witness."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Right. Would you say his time in parole was well-spent? No trouble, not running with the wrong crowd… Stable employment? I noticed he's listed as living with his mother."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Was thinking about my interaction with the vet- would I normally introduce myself to such a contact as Agent Kendall or Agent Cliff
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: "He was slumped with bond debt and a huge fine over a misdemeanor but he got out of it quick. He was working as a tattoo artist in a legit place. Got out of the ditch eventually."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: kendall
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Did he ever mention any friends or coworkers to you that stood out? Maybe the type of people he shouldn't be around. Foreign nationals, so on."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "No, they typically don't do that to their parole officer, Agent. You and I know they present themselves to me as the best versions of themselves, as per their lawyer."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Good try, though."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "It's a tragedy what's happening to these kids. I appreciate your time. We're just trying to get all the facts straight." He pauses. "If you think of anything that you feel the local PD might've overlooked, if you remember anything about him not reflected in the case or statements… Don't be shy to reach out."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "It's a sad, sad thing but he did have high potential to offend again."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I hope it's sorted out soon without anyone hurt."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Before you go--"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "One last thing. You said he was working as a tattoo artist. Do you remember the place?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Uh- let me see…"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
"It says…. 'Angular Atelier'. I really don't know what it's like but it's somewhere near…"

You note the address down.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You take care, ma'am."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Thanks. Bye."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's up north in the hood, a different postcode but the same dog shit regardless.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Marking on map…
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Is everyone grouped up right now?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Depends.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You can individually achieve things.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan suggests Earle or McCannon run the revolver's serial number to see if it's stolen or a straw purchase from a POI. He also wants to talk to the mother, but ideally in person with another agent. That's a better way to do business with a family member.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: We need these pills checked by the local narco-forensics, as well.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Finnegan, you're going to interview the mother.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Others, list actions now.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon wants to check that tattoo shop.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Samantha. Roll INT, blind.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: At the Motel on his laptop. He does as Finnegan asks and then, if he has the time spare, tries running the keyword 'reverb' through a few drug markets and forums on TOR to see if there's any talk of the stuff online.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Who wants to listen to the radio?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug ABSOLUTELY does.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI
YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

Samantha appears to be in her thirties with a comely nose and a sharp face. She's of average height, and aging has only recently started to creep in her features. She's of average weight, with dirty blonde hair and brown eyes. Furrows have started to form on her temple.

Samantha was interested in medicine from the moment

she listened to her father's heartbeat through his

stethescope. Smart and disciplined, she pushed through

a difficult education to become a trauma surgeon at the

NYU Grossman School of Medicine. By her early

thirties, she had already carved herself a reputation as a

skilled clinician and an accomplished researcher,

working to further the field of emergency medicine.

That reputation was tested the night her husband was

brought into her own hospital. He had been attacked,

initial reports indicating a mugging-gone-wrong.

Samantha was on call and prepared to operate, but

what she found was wrong; his bones and organs were

liquefied, and his vascular system ruptured in patterns

no aneurysm or illness could possibly explain.

She barely had time to process it before the body was

taken from her custody. Within hours, the chart was

scrubbed, and official records listed his death as a “

catastrophic hemorrhage.” Samantha, however,

remembered every detail. She knew what she saw, and

she knew someone else had made sure she wouldn't be

allowed to prove it.

Crushed but undeterred, she redirected her career.

Using her skills and connections, she entered the FBI’

Criminal Investigative Division as a forensic medical

specialist. For her past colleagues, it was a career

move. Secretly, it was a window for her to pursue her

own investigations regarding her husband's death.

Without telling anyone, she dug through case files:

unexplained autopsies, anomalies in forensic reports,

events that echoed what she’d seen on her husband’

s table.

She never said a word of her search to colleagues,

friends, or family. But Delta Green noticed.

Unauthorized queries, repeated hits on redacted case

numbers, her name appearing again and again where it

shouldn’t. They had already erased her husband’s

corpse, his grave had always been empty. Now, they

noticed they had left a loose end.

When they finally reached out, Samantha didn’t resist.

She'd been waiting for someone to admit what she

already knew: her husband’s death wasn’t natural.

Husband's death preceded Samantha's induction into the FBI and Delta Green by a few years. (Inducted into the FBI in 2000, DG in 2006) Before that time, the family was peaceful. Afterwards, she decided to send her son to boarding school, leaving home at the age of 13. She only sees her son in the summers, with the rare visit to his out-of-state school. Nowadays he's off to college, calling only out of necessity and a need for money. He's still affectionate towards her, but resents her for leaving him all by himself. One could say she doesn't know her own son.

messages.content: Hmm… What are my options?
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Well to assume "The News" isn't a radio channel
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Mainstream latin hiphop
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Well, mainstream it is.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: The news are full of the upcoming election.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The United States is excited for its first Black president.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: All the power to all the people.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Samantha.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You wholeheartedly do not think you can get away trace-free out of analyzing drugs in a DEA lab. And, you're out of your FBI tickets too in New Mexico.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: UNM Hospital lab seems like the only option without exiting the operation zone.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Luckily you are a MD. Getting in should only be a matter of…
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Let's say that combined with a labcoat and a DEA badge you can do some things that leave spy movies to shame.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Hit a blind Bureucracy roll. It should help with a temporary ID card.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

Samantha appears to be in her thirties with a comely nose and a sharp face. She's of average height, and aging has only recently started to creep in her features. She's of average weight, with dirty blonde hair and brown eyes. Furrows have started to form on her temple.

Samantha was interested in medicine from the moment

she listened to her father's heartbeat through his

stethescope. Smart and disciplined, she pushed through

a difficult education to become a trauma surgeon at the

NYU Grossman School of Medicine. By her early

thirties, she had already carved herself a reputation as a

skilled clinician and an accomplished researcher,

working to further the field of emergency medicine.

That reputation was tested the night her husband was

brought into her own hospital. He had been attacked,

initial reports indicating a mugging-gone-wrong.

Samantha was on call and prepared to operate, but

what she found was wrong; his bones and organs were

liquefied, and his vascular system ruptured in patterns

no aneurysm or illness could possibly explain.

She barely had time to process it before the body was

taken from her custody. Within hours, the chart was

scrubbed, and official records listed his death as a “

catastrophic hemorrhage.” Samantha, however,

remembered every detail. She knew what she saw, and

she knew someone else had made sure she wouldn't be

allowed to prove it.

Crushed but undeterred, she redirected her career.

Using her skills and connections, she entered the FBI’

Criminal Investigative Division as a forensic medical

specialist. For her past colleagues, it was a career

move. Secretly, it was a window for her to pursue her

own investigations regarding her husband's death.

Without telling anyone, she dug through case files:

unexplained autopsies, anomalies in forensic reports,

events that echoed what she’d seen on her husband’

s table.

She never said a word of her search to colleagues,

friends, or family. But Delta Green noticed.

Unauthorized queries, repeated hits on redacted case

numbers, her name appearing again and again where it

shouldn’t. They had already erased her husband’s

corpse, his grave had always been empty. Now, they

noticed they had left a loose end.

When they finally reached out, Samantha didn’t resist.

She'd been waiting for someone to admit what she

already knew: her husband’s death wasn’t natural.

Husband's death preceded Samantha's induction into the FBI and Delta Green by a few years. (Inducted into the FBI in 2000, DG in 2006) Before that time, the family was peaceful. Afterwards, she decided to send her son to boarding school, leaving home at the age of 13. She only sees her son in the summers, with the rare visit to his out-of-state school. Nowadays he's off to college, calling only out of necessity and a need for money. He's still affectionate towards her, but resents her for leaving him all by himself. One could say she doesn't know her own son.

messages.content: Samantha. You are in.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: That big boxy machine in the back, that's an X-ray crystallography machine.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's to do molecular analysis.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I am still dressed in a suit?
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: You're in a labcoat. It hides your suit.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: No one has said a thing to you other than security.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Alright. Seems I haven't gone stupid.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: I'll work with the machine casually, walking around the room to gather things if need be. I try not to make eye contact or get too close to anyone who may be nearby.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Interns rush in and out. Doctors are nowhere to be seen. Probably in for the polyclinic hours.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Would this be regular in a lab, a technician rushing some analysis?
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: Not one of them question you, or dare to do so.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Your credidentials just say "TEMPORARY", you can roll with whatever the hell you want. But it's factual that you are a M.D.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: For the analysis work itself. You have a baggy of 5 Skypes.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I'll crack one in half and use it with the machine.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: With this equipment, you'd be rolling at a 80% on Medicine. Go ahead and shoot on public.

Criminal Investigative Division","nationality":"American - New York","sex":"F","age":"36 - October 13 1971","education":"NYU Grossman School of Medicine."},"corruption":{"value":0,"haveSeenTheYellowSign":false,"gift":"","insight":""},"physicalDescription":"

Samantha appears to be in her thirties with a comely nose and a sharp face. She's of average height, and aging has only recently started to creep in her features. She's of average weight, with dirty blonde hair and brown eyes. Furrows have started to form on her temple.

Samantha was interested in medicine from the moment

she listened to her father's heartbeat through his

stethescope. Smart and disciplined, she pushed through

a difficult education to become a trauma surgeon at the

NYU Grossman School of Medicine. By her early

thirties, she had already carved herself a reputation as a

skilled clinician and an accomplished researcher,

working to further the field of emergency medicine.

That reputation was tested the night her husband was

brought into her own hospital. He had been attacked,

initial reports indicating a mugging-gone-wrong.

Samantha was on call and prepared to operate, but

what she found was wrong; his bones and organs were

liquefied, and his vascular system ruptured in patterns

no aneurysm or illness could possibly explain.

She barely had time to process it before the body was

taken from her custody. Within hours, the chart was

scrubbed, and official records listed his death as a “

catastrophic hemorrhage.” Samantha, however,

remembered every detail. She knew what she saw, and

she knew someone else had made sure she wouldn't be

allowed to prove it.

Crushed but undeterred, she redirected her career.

Using her skills and connections, she entered the FBI’

Criminal Investigative Division as a forensic medical

specialist. For her past colleagues, it was a career

move. Secretly, it was a window for her to pursue her

own investigations regarding her husband's death.

Without telling anyone, she dug through case files:

unexplained autopsies, anomalies in forensic reports,

events that echoed what she’d seen on her husband’

s table.

She never said a word of her search to colleagues,

friends, or family. But Delta Green noticed.

Unauthorized queries, repeated hits on redacted case

numbers, her name appearing again and again where it

shouldn’t. They had already erased her husband’s

corpse, his grave had always been empty. Now, they

noticed they had left a loose end.

When they finally reached out, Samantha didn’t resist.

She'd been waiting for someone to admit what she

already knew: her husband’s death wasn’t natural.

Husband's death preceded Samantha's induction into the FBI and Delta Green by a few years. (Inducted into the FBI in 2000, DG in 2006) Before that time, the family was peaceful. Afterwards, she decided to send her son to boarding school, leaving home at the age of 13. She only sees her son in the summers, with the rare visit to his out-of-state school. Nowadays he's off to college, calling only out of necessity and a need for money. He's still affectionate towards her, but resents her for leaving him all by himself. One could say she doesn't know her own son.

Samantha appears to be in her thirties with a comely nose and a sharp face. She's of average height, and aging has only recently started to creep in her features. She's of average weight, with dirty blonde hair and brown eyes. Furrows have started to form on her temple.

Samantha was interested in medicine from the moment

she listened to her father's heartbeat through his

stethescope. Smart and disciplined, she pushed through

a difficult education to become a trauma surgeon at the

NYU Grossman School of Medicine. By her early

thirties, she had already carved herself a reputation as a

skilled clinician and an accomplished researcher,

working to further the field of emergency medicine.

That reputation was tested the night her husband was

brought into her own hospital. He had been attacked,

initial reports indicating a mugging-gone-wrong.

Samantha was on call and prepared to operate, but

what she found was wrong; his bones and organs were

liquefied, and his vascular system ruptured in patterns

no aneurysm or illness could possibly explain.

She barely had time to process it before the body was

taken from her custody. Within hours, the chart was

scrubbed, and official records listed his death as a “

catastrophic hemorrhage.” Samantha, however,

remembered every detail. She knew what she saw, and

she knew someone else had made sure she wouldn't be

allowed to prove it.

Crushed but undeterred, she redirected her career.

Using her skills and connections, she entered the FBI’

Criminal Investigative Division as a forensic medical

specialist. For her past colleagues, it was a career

move. Secretly, it was a window for her to pursue her

own investigations regarding her husband's death.

Without telling anyone, she dug through case files:

unexplained autopsies, anomalies in forensic reports,

events that echoed what she’d seen on her husband’

s table.

She never said a word of her search to colleagues,

friends, or family. But Delta Green noticed.

Unauthorized queries, repeated hits on redacted case

numbers, her name appearing again and again where it

shouldn’t. They had already erased her husband’s

corpse, his grave had always been empty. Now, they

noticed they had left a loose end.

When they finally reached out, Samantha didn’t resist.

She'd been waiting for someone to admit what she

already knew: her husband’s death wasn’t natural.

Husband's death preceded Samantha's induction into the FBI and Delta Green by a few years. (Inducted into the FBI in 2000, DG in 2006) Before that time, the family was peaceful. Afterwards, she decided to send her son to boarding school, leaving home at the age of 13. She only sees her son in the summers, with the rare visit to his out-of-state school. Nowadays he's off to college, calling only out of necessity and a need for money. He's still affectionate towards her, but resents her for leaving him all by himself. One could say she doesn't know her own son.

messages.content: Cliff.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The freezing cold of perfect understanding hits you like an elbow to the stomach.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It looks like you are at the limit of science itself.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You decide to get on with the report.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Really nothing I can do? Put it through this machine and use that test chemical and whatnot
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: The pill itself contains trace MDMA and large amounts of sugar.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It also includes something entirely else.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Ignore the title, it says UNM Biochemical.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Looks like you have finally found what you came here for.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: With the report, I will casually leave the premises.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: A few side-eyes tail you as you exit the campus.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's about afternoon for you, but everyone else, it's around 9 where we left.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Earle. We are resolving your effort up next.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Where do you wish to analyze the footage?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: At the safehouse, away from prying eyes.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: The safehouse has no law enforcement level digital forensics to identify this woman.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: There is still a long way to go until you can dox people just like that, it's 2008.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: In which case I presumably don't have a choice other than to try with the police or FBI offices. How much social engineering is it gonna take to get their help here?
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: You're not gonna waltz in the FBI Field Office without your ID and use their computer lab. That's next to impossible. However, you could enforce jurisdiction over the case with a Law or Bureucracy roll at the ABQPD SEHQ, or just go ahead and do your thing at DEA Field Office, but you'll still need some jurisdiction to act on a police case. And, if you fail this last one, it might trigger red flags.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: There is a much more far out and nuclear option like way to go about this, but I'll leave that for you to figure out. It is after 9/11 indeed.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: At 80% CS its hard for you to fumble this.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I know very little about the small-p politics that'd get me into one of those offices and a lot about the post-2001 surveillance state. I'm gonna try and break into one of Palantir, NSA-style databases that might have accrued some information on our mystery Jane Doe.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: What a funny way to say that you're using the DEA computer lab. Breaking into a NSA-level database…
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Yeah that
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Earle, you're not breaking into shit. You're at the Simms building. You may work your magic.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A radio plays this in the computer lab.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The program is fairly simple to use. A CS roll will do the trick.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd
messages.content:
CRITICAL SUCCESS!

Slightly overweight, brown hair combed to one side, chevron moustache.

a- Born 1980 in Paris Texas to a single mother. Rough upbringing led him to (mostly) forswear drugs and alcohol, developed a complex against middle America, 'hicks' etc.

- Became interested in computer science during the dot-com bubble and left home to study I.T at 18.

- Married in 2003 while working the help-desk at Cisco. Made the majority of his income at this time via cable piracy - running services that could decrypt smart cards, set-top boxes etc.

- Became interested in libertarianism and conspiracy culture at around this time, which tied into much of his hacking work; claims to have worked with Gary McKinnon, among others.

- Joined FBI Operational Technology division in 2005, in part for work experience and in part to enter the 'belly of beast' as far as his interests are concerned ('is the government really messing with the weather?' etc).

- Continues to work in this capacity alongside his side-hustles; regarded by colleagues as reliable, if a little eccentric.

messages.content: It's pretty much retard proofed. Your luck stems from the fact that out of all days, today is when it's not lagging and your query is processed in just two hours instead of up to 16.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Several hits.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The one that catches your attention is pretty much the exact same woman in the video.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Jane Margolis, 26.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The radio is turned off by another agent.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The woman on the screen… Unemployed, did some community service hours over a petty offence a few years ago followed by dozens of attended rehab meetings.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Goes without saying she is a potential prime victim of a drug related scheme.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You get a printout of her file and phone McCannon. But not before…
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A Hispanic agent is staring you down from down the hallway.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You don't know eachother. But your pasty white skin clearly doesn't scream New Mexico.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He stares right back at him without much care for how he might look right now. "Yeah?"
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: He buries his face back into his paperwork and slowly walks away into another office space.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Mhm."
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Back to calling McCannon.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Actually, you flip your phone open, but before you call anyone…
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: We are panning to McCannon.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon. You're in front of the tattoo joint.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Is it open?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: No. The junkie-in-charge is probably sleeping and tossing around and farting in his stoner apartment.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The front-everything is barred. No shutters.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You're in the Corolla, staring it down from a street away.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: No movement.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A few dogs bark and a kid skitters around the place.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I can spin the block and check the back of the store, maybe.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: There is no "back of the store", behind is an apartment and the back is in a tight alley.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Noted.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Does it look like it has been in operation at all recently?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Roll Search.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

Brown hair and small, baby blue eyes, of average height and build.

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

messages.content: It's used but you can't tell how often.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Are the operating times listed anywhere?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: No. Probably open whenever the owner is not stoned out of his mind and closed whenever he is.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Knowing junkies he's probably passed out right inside. McCannon will try  knocking.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: You hear a radio somewhere around the block.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You knock on the barred window. No response after 10 seconds.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He'll check the back alley.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Maybe there's a service entrance.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: One building code incompilant fire exit.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: On a heads, you were smart enough to bring the Halligan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

rolls: {"class":"Roll","options":{},"dice":[],"formula":"1d2","terms":[{"class":"Die","options":{"flavor":null},"evaluated":true,"number":1,"faces":2,"modifiers":[],"results":[{"result":1,"active":true}]}],"total":1,"evaluated":true}
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's still in the chevy.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Which is down several blocks driven by Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Sucks.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: He'll try knocking on the service exit just in case.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content:
No response. A hispanic kid runs up a few dozen meters away from you and claims:

"Izz not open sir."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Oh yeah?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "You come later!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "When's it open, kid?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "It opens at 5."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You know anything about the owner? Who works here?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: The kid inexplicably lets out a shriek and runs away from you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon looks behind himself quickly.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: No one behind. You realize that it's just hood life in vivo.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You don't answer questions like that around here.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Retarded ass kids.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Oh well.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Where was Finnegan stomping around again?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: As this is happening he is already at that womans door with Doug. You could still do other things.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Well, barring breaking in through the front McCannon deigns to see if he can't figure out something useful to do until five. How did Samantha get to the hospital?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Bus over IS40N, she did have some time to figure out the city yesterday. You can take a cab, but right now, she is probably deep in work.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: If you have no other actions, we are panning over to Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon isn't leaving the Civic to have it's tires replaced with bricks.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Then you are staking out the tattoo joint?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Might as well wait around.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: You mean Corolla.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Civic is the missing kids car.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: In any case, we are panning over.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Yeah
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Finnegan, Doug.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The old woman opens the door for you after you ask for her.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Hello there, good morning. Yes?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Let's see what Doug says first.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Would the woman find anything at all weird in two government-looking men visiting her home at 9 of the morning?
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: What do you think.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: We try to look professional. "Ma'am, good morning. Agent Callahan, DEA. This is my partner."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Agent Moore, DEA."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Oh- the DEA…"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Oh no…"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: She is visibly despaired at the mention.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Oh, no, no, please. Just some questions we have to ask. It's nothing like you think."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "He's not being charged and he's not under investigation for anything in our neck of the woods." He forces a sympathetic smile.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: She is much too used to the sight.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "My poor boy…"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Well then what is it?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Do you mind if we come inside?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Sure, come in…"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You're inside in the living room. It's generic Americana. Paint the picture.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Consider it painted.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Photos of Damien are all over the place, in standing frames.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I'm going to ask you a few questions about Damien. It's important for him that you're as honest as possible with us."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Would we, for whatever reason, require pictures of Damien. All we're working on is that grainy photo in the MPR, right?
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Would you like some coffee? I just put the pot on."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "If you don't mind, ma'am, I'll take some."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: The photos don't really offer anything new for you, you already have a quite recent one.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Thanks, I'll be fine."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: It's mostly childhood friends.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug won't have no coffee.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: She pours one for Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Did he go out often at night? Weeknights, weekends?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Oh yes, he's an outgoing child."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "He used to have bad friends before he went to jail, but after that he assured me he'd only deal with good people…"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Did he ever go out with friends, or people you might know or recognize? Within the last month or two, please."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "He told me he was going to have some friends over at a club about dusk the day he disappeared… other than that I'm not sure if I know any of his friends."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Any… particular interests you've ever noticed in Damien? What kind of boy was he to you?"
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "He didn't come back for so late so I just went to the police immediately."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan rubs his forehead and glares at Doug.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Oh he's my little artist."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "He's just the artsy type."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "He loves to draw."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Ma'am, when the police took the report from you, did they look through his personal effects at all?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Personal effects such as?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "His room. His car, if it was parked here."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "No, they did not go through his room."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Would you mind if we gave it a once-over? I want to be clear - he's not in any trouble, he's not being charged, he just got off parole and his social worker said he seemed to be doing well. We're just trying to connect some dots."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Public, Persuade.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

messages.content: "Oh he would hate me for saying it but… just a quick peek please."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I want my boy back…"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Agent Moore would like to ask you a few more questions. I'll only be a few minutes." He leans over to Doug and whispers. "Ask about extended family, anything about his work."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Doug, no need to drag it out. The boy is pretty much alienated from her and it's apparent to you that the arrangement goes like this: he makes her happy and she keeps him housed.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan, onwards to his room.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Good work Doug, keeping her busy in the other room.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Here you are.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The smell of unwashed clothes and BO reminds you of college.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: What a mess. Is everything in the image on the table to look at?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: The image is representative of the mess, you never know the ingenious hiding spots that junkies come up with.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: On the lookout for: Personal electronics, ashtrays, drug paraphanalia.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Public Search.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.

messages.content:
Hidden compartment in the dresser: bong and an ounce of weed. It's unmistakably marijuana, and this amount totally goes over intent to distribute.

There is something inside the wall.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You have no idea how to get your hand inside there without ripping the drywall clean. But it's behind there.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I wonder how he's been getting it in and out, himself. Let me feel around for a tool.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: A tool like what?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Something rigid and durable, like a bulky flathead, a smoke store folder knife.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: You find a prybar, the kind that burglars love, in one of the drawers.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's solid and heavy in the hand.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He lines it up above where he thinks the cavity is and intends to give it one kick forceful enough to let him pry the rest out.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Roll Strength.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.

messages.content: You bust whatever is inside and it spills out.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Skype pills.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: At least another hundred.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Every good agent has a small flashlight. I check inside the cavity for anything else he shoved into the crevices.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: 2000$ in cash and a box of .380 cartridges.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Is there reasonably enough time to check one or two more things?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: There is reasonably enough time to get all the Evil Ecstasy Pills out of this womans house.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Or leave them as is and risk catastrophe.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Better bag up all this dope before his poor mother catches wind of it. The pills, obviously, are coming with me.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: No cellphone or laptop?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Doesn't take much finesse to scoop them all in.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: There's a desktop. You don't have enough time to recover it discreetly.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Damn. Time to go.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Anything else you would like to do here?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug, any especially good questions?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Not particularly, no. Doesn't seem like Damien was "employed" in any standard capacity.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Guys a fucking drug dealer anyone with 1/4th of a brain can tell that
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: That's just the answers I got.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Extended family is all way out of state, nothing that appears possible to follow up on.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Ma'am, thank you for your time. This has been very helpful. We're on the right track."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Oh please, thank you, thank you…"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: She sees you outside.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: About noon.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon. You receive a call. It's Earle, frantically giving you an adress to meet at.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's a suburb at the edge of Sandia Heights.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Rest of you, sans David and Cliff meet up on location.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: That's her place.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: How do you go about this?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: No partner on record. Probably alone and asleep in there, right now. If she is ignoring rehab.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: How's it looking? A single-unit house?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Two units, one house seperated in half. It's in New Mexico desert style.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The other half seems vacant.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan suggests one or two people go around the back in case she tries to "book it". There's some Newark in the way he says it.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Earle and Doug are on it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You and McCannon are knocking up front.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Knock-knock.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "One sec I'm coming!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The door opens.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan gives the same introduction he's been giving all damn day.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Um, am I under arrest?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan, it's either this or that. There are two agents behind her house.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: As long as she doesn't bitch about a warrant. That's the American way.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: We're evil feds. We do not give one fuck about a warrant.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Once they're situated, he shows her the picture of Damien Lucas and asks if she's ever seen him before.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: David has been at work. You either bag her right now or it's a civilized discussion. Make the call.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I think we should grab her. At worst, she's going to file a complaint that she was arrested for no reason and asked questions.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Go right on.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Right now, you're being detained. I need you to turn away from the sound of my voice and keep your arms outstretched."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Uh… shit…"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: She hesitantly complies.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I need to call my dad and my lawyer."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan steps in for the collar. Right hand, left hand. "I understand. You'll get to do both shortly."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: He isn't going to mirandize her if she doesn't ask about it; this is extralegal.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: There is no fighting back whatsoever. She has no clue.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You load her in the back of the chevy and drive off out the neighbourhood.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Another fine days work.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Reverberations - Session 2 End.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
